description.description_en: Annual or biennial herbs, glabrous, whitish or glauous; stems 4-angled, many-branched, prostrate at base, 10–30 cm long.Leaves opposite, sessile, ovate, 10–25 mm long, 5–15 mm wide, spreading, margins entire, apex acute to subobtuse, base rounded.Flowers axillary, pedicel 2–3 cm long; calyx segments linear-lanceolate, long-acuminate, 4–6 mm long; corolla bluish-purple to reddish, lobes obovate-orbicular, apex serrate, often ciliolate.Capsules globose, dehiscence circumscissile; seeds small, dark brown.
